This project is a single-page landing site for Pilates Academy® Meydan, a boutique
Pilates studio in Dubai and a branch of Pilates Academy® Dubai (pilatesacademydubai.com).

Everything lives in index.html — HTML, CSS (in a <style> block), and the booking form.
There is no build step and no framework. Keep it a single self-contained file.

When the user asks for changes, edit index.html directly and keep these constraints:

DESIGN / BRAND
- Fonts: Cormorant Garamond for headings, Jost for body. Don't introduce new fonts.
- Colors are CSS variables in :root. Reuse them; don't hardcode new hex values unless asked.
  ink #2A2E33, soft #5C636B, aqua #7FC9C9, aqua-deep #3E8E8E,
  gold #C9A24B, gold-soft #D8BC7E, paper #FFFFFF, mist #EEF3F3.
- Aesthetic: airy, light, premium, editorial. Big serif headlines with gold italic accents.
- Tagline: "Rooted in Tradition, Inspired by Innovation." Keep the crown + "Pilates Academy / Meydan" lockup.

FORM
- The booking form posts to Formspree. The action URL contains YOUR_FORM_ID as a placeholder
  the user must replace with their real Formspree endpoint. Don't remove the form or change
  the field `name` attributes (name, phone, email, program) unless asked.

LAYOUT
- It must stay a single-screen-first landing page: the booking form should remain visible
  in the hero, above the fold, on load. Don't bury it.
- Keep it responsive (the existing @media breakpoints at 920px and 560px).

ANIMATIONS
- Fade-in uses `.fade` with `animation-fill-mode: both` so content never gets stuck invisible.
  Preserve that — never set a permanent opacity:0 on hero content.

When swapping in real images (hero photo, logo), reference files placed in this same folder
by relative path (e.g. src="logo.png", or background-image:url('hero.jpg')).
